{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-sistent-component-js-content-file-path-src-collections-sistent-components-badge-code-mdx","path":"/projects/sistent/components/badge/code","result":{"data":{"mdx":{"body":"\nimport { Badge, Avatar } from \"@sistent/sistent\";\nimport MailIcon from \"@mui/icons-material/Mail\";\n\n\nBadges display counts, small information indicators, or status markers that are attached to other interface elements.\n\n<a id=\"Basic Badge\">\n  <h2>Basic Badge</h2>\n</a>\n\nExamples of badges containing text, primarily using the badgeContent prop.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"primary\">\n        <MailIcon />\n      </Badge>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"basic-badge\" collapsible code={`<Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"primary\">\n  <MailIcon />\n</Badge>`} />\n</div>\n\n<h3>Dot Badge</h3>\nThe dot badge shows a small dot indicator without any content.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <Badge variant=\"dot\" color=\"secondary\">\n        <MailIcon />\n      </Badge>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"dot-badge\" collapsible code={`<Badge variant=\"dot\" color=\"secondary\">\n  <MailIcon />\n</Badge>`} />\n</div>\n\n<h3>Badge Colors</h3>\nUse the color prop to apply theme palette colors to badges.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: '20px' }}>\n        <Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"primary\">\n        <MailIcon />\n        </Badge>\n        <Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"secondary\">\n        <MailIcon />\n        </Badge>\n        <Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"error\">\n        <MailIcon />\n        </Badge>\n        <Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"warning\">\n        <MailIcon />\n        </Badge>\n        <Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"success\">\n        <MailIcon />\n        </Badge>\n      </div>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"badge-colors\" collapsible code={`<Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"primary\" />\n<Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"secondary\" />\n<Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"error\" />\n<Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"warning\" />\n<Badge badgeContent={4} color=\"success\" />`} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Badge Position\">\n  <h2>Badge Position</h2>\n</a>\n\nUse the anchorOrigin prop to change the position of the badge.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n      <div style={{ display: 'flex', gap: '20px' }}>\n        <Badge\n          badgeContent={4}\n          color=\"primary\"\n          anchorOrigin={{\n            vertical: \"top\",\n            horizontal: \"right\",\n          }}\n        >\n          <MailIcon />\n        </Badge>\n        <Badge\n          badgeContent={4}\n          color=\"primary\"\n          anchorOrigin={{\n            vertical: \"top\",\n            horizontal: \"left\",\n          }}\n        >\n          <MailIcon />\n        </Badge>\n        <Badge\n          badgeContent={4}\n          color=\"primary\"\n          anchorOrigin={{\n            vertical: \"bottom\",\n            horizontal: \"right\",\n          }}\n        >\n          <MailIcon />\n        </Badge>\n        <Badge\n          badgeContent={4}\n          color=\"primary\"\n          anchorOrigin={{\n            vertical: \"bottom\",\n            horizontal: \"left\",\n          }}\n        >\n          <MailIcon />\n        </Badge>\n      </div>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"badge-position\" collapsible code={`<Badge \n  badgeContent={4} \n  color=\"primary\"\n  anchorOrigin={{\n    vertical: 'top',\n    horizontal: 'right',\n  }}\n>\n  <MailIcon />\n</Badge>`} />\n</div>\n\n<a id=\"Badge with Avatar\">\n  <h2>Badge with Avatar</h2>\n</a>\n\nBadges can be used with avatars to show user status.\n\n<div className=\"showcase\">\n  <div className=\"items\">\n    <ThemeWrapper>\n        <Badge\n          overlap=\"circular\"\n          anchorOrigin={{ vertical: \"bottom\", horizontal: \"right\" }}\n          variant=\"dot\"\n          color=\"success\"\n        >\n          <Avatar>U</Avatar>\n        </Badge>\n    </ThemeWrapper>\n  </div>\n  <CodeBlock name=\"badge-avatar\" collapsible code={`<Badge\n    overlap=\"circular\"\n    anchorOrigin={{ vertical: 'bottom', horizontal: 'right' }}\n    variant=\"dot\"\n    color=\"success\"\n  >\n    <Avatar>U</Avatar>\n  </Badge>`} />\n</div>\n","frontmatter":{"title":"Badge Code","description":"A badge is a small piece of information that is used to convey a specific message or status. It is often used to provide additional context or information about an item, such as a notification count, status indicator, or label."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/sistent/components/badge/code","componentName":"badge","availablePages":["code","guidance","overview"],"frontmatter":{"title":"Badge Code","component":"badge","description":"A badge is a small piece of information that is used to convey a specific message or status. It is often used to provide additional context or information about an item, such as a notification count, status indicator, or label."}}},"staticQueryHashes":["4152005505","934084603"],"slicesMap":{}}